---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy - The Realm of Patterns" description="How we collect, use, and protect your data at The Realm of Patterns.">
  <div class="legal-page">
    <div class="page-container">
      <header class="page-header">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="effective-date">Effective Date: February 4, 2026</p>
      </header>

      <div class="legal-content">
        <section>
          <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
          <p>
            The Realm of Patterns ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy.
            This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information
            when you use our website and services.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>

          <h3>2.1 Information You Provide</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Birth Data:</strong> Date, time, and location of birth (required for pattern calculations)</li>
            <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Email address (for account creation and communication)</li>
            <li><strong>Check-in Responses:</strong> Your answers to the 8-question daily check-in</li>
            <li><strong>Payment Information:</strong> Processed securely through Stripe; we don't store credit card numbers</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>2.2 Information Collected Automatically</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Pages visited, features used, time spent</li>
            <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Browser type, operating system, screen size</li>
            <li><strong>IP Address:</strong> For security and approximate location (country level)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Calculate your 16-dimensional cosmic pattern</li>
            <li>Provide personalized readings and recommendations</li>
            <li>Track your pattern over time (history feature)</li>
            <li>Process payments and manage subscriptions</li>
            <li>Send service-related communications</li>
            <li>Improve our services through aggregated analytics</li>
            <li>Prevent fraud and ensure security</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
          <p>We do not sell your personal data. We share information only in these limited circumstances:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> Stripe (payments), Cloudflare (hosting), necessary third parties</li>
            <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> When required by law or to protect rights</li>
            <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In connection with mergers or acquisitions</li>
            <li><strong>With Your Consent:</strong> When you explicitly agree to sharing</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>5. Circle (Team) Features</h2>
          <p>
            If you join a Circle, certain pattern data may be visible to other Circle members as part
            of the shared dashboard feature. You can control what is shared through your privacy settings.
            Circle facilitators can see aggregated coherence metrics but not individual check-in responses
            unless you choose to share them.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>6. Data Storage and Security</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Data is stored on Cloudflare infrastructure with encryption at rest</li>
            <li>We use HTTPS for all data transmission</li>
            <li>Access to personal data is restricted to authorized personnel</li>
            <li>We conduct regular security reviews</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>
            We retain your data as long as your account is active or as needed to provide services.
            After account deletion, we retain data for up to 30 days for backup purposes, then permanently delete it.
            Aggregated, anonymized data may be retained indefinitely for research and improvement.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>You have the right to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of your personal data</li>
            <li><strong>Export:</strong> Download your data in portable formats (Pattern-Keeper+)</li>
            <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Update inaccurate information</li>
            <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your account and data</li>
            <li><strong>Opt-out:</strong> Unsubscribe from marketing communications</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>9. Cookies and Local Storage</h2>
          <p>We use:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Essential cookies:</strong> For authentication and security</li>
            <li><strong>Local storage:</strong> For preferences, mode selection, and offline functionality</li>
            <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> To understand usage patterns (can be disabled)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>10. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Our services are not intended for users under 13. We do not knowingly collect data from children.
            If we learn we have collected data from a child under 13, we will delete it promptly.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>11. International Users</h2>
          <p>
            Our services are hosted globally via Cloudflare. By using our services, you consent to
            the transfer of your data to servers that may be located outside your country of residence.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>12. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will notify you of material changes
            via email or prominent notice on our website. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>13. Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            For privacy-related questions or to exercise your rights, contact us at:
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Email:</strong> privacy@therealmofpatterns.com
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    --gold: #d4a854;
    --dark: #0a0908;
    --dark-surface: #141210;
    --text: #f0e8d8;
    --text-muted: rgba(240, 232, 216, 0.6);

    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif;
    background: var(--dark);
    color: var(--text);
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 6rem 2rem 4rem;
  }

  .page-container {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .page-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(212, 168, 84, 0.2);
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', Georgia, serif;
  }

  .effective-date {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .legal-content section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-content h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-content p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-content ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-content li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content li strong {
    color: var(--text);
  }
</style>
